<p>The <code>array</code> tag retrieves multiple rows from the database.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}array "columns from table where condition"{close}
  {open}$column1{close} - {open}$column2{close}
{open}/array{close}</pre>

<h2>Example: User List</h2>
<pre>{open}array "name&comma; email from users"{close}
  &lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;{open}$name{close}&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;{open}$email{close}&lt;/td&gt;
  &lt;/tr&gt;
{open}else{close}
  &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td colspan="2"&gt;No users found&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
{open}/array{close}</pre>

<h2>With Options</h2>
<pre>{open}array "* from products", sort='price', rows=10{close}
  {open}$name{close}: ${open}$price{close}
{open}/array{close}</pre>

<h2>PHP Variable Method</h2>
<pre>// In PHP:
$users = db("array * from users");

// In template:
{open}users{close}
  {open}$name{close}
{open}/users{close}</pre>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Use &amp;comma; to escape commas in template syntax.</p>
<p>Supports all iteration properties ({open}first{close}, {open}last{close}, {open}&amp;count{close}, etc.)</p>
